        <updateDate>2023-08-10T14:33:46Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Pistol Brace Protection Act</b></p> <p>This bill removes certain brace-equipped firearms from regulation under certain federal firearms laws. </p> <p>Specifically, under the bill, a pistol that that is equipped with an attachable stabilizing brace (or arm brace) that allows the pistol to be fired with one hand is not a rifle or shotgun subject to regulation (e.g., registration requirements) under the&nbsp;National&nbsp;Firearms&nbsp;Act. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
